# Environment Variables Template for Render

## Production (Render)
```
DB_HOST=dpg-your-id.render.internal
DB_USER=admin
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_password
DB_NAME=expense_tracker
DB_PORT=3306
NODE_ENV=production
```

## Development (Local)
```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_local_password
DB_NAME=expense_tracker
DB_PORT=3306
NODE_ENV=development
```

## Notes
- Get `DB_HOST` from Render MySQL service page (use Internal Database URL)
- Never commit `.env` â€” only push `.env.example`
- For Render, set variables in the dashboard, not in `.env` file
